We think many Nigerians are ignorant about the BVN (Bank Verification Number). It is simply a unique identifier number to each individual.
Your BVN is a unique identifier and that's why State governments use it to fight ghost workers. Good day.
Go to any bank to inquire if anyone else can use your BVN other than you. It is your unique identifier.
It is your ATM/Debit card details like number, PIN and CVC codes that can be used to scam you.
Don't be ignorant, your BVN cannot be used to scam you. It is a unique identifier and not an access token.
